Because the sum represents the number of 'excess' steps forward over backward up to that point, and you can't have negative steps. So the code's loop is:

for each j in 0..n-1:

sum += a[j]

if (sum <0) { result = false; break; }

if (sum ==0) { check remaining elements are zero. break; }

So the code's missing condition is checking whether sum <0.
